725703f-a.title: Queens: 88th Avenue - Ransom Street
725703f-a.text:
88th Avenue, at the N.E. corner of Ransom Street, Creed.
moor, showing the Creedmoor Park Restaurant, most likely the
B. Kissam property of 1891.
P. L. Sperr  June 6, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS

727868f-b.title: Queens: Ransom Street - 88th Avenue
727868f-b.text:
Ransom Street (Shaler Street), at the S.E. corner of Eighty-eimhth
Ave. showing what Eugene L. Armbruster states doubtfully to be the
A. Graf house in 1896 and the old Eissam House before that. There are
33.1 acres of ground belonging to the B.T. Kissam Estate,south of
Eighty-eighth Ave. to Braddock Ave. (Rocky Rill Road in 1909.) On this
property there were two dwellings, one east of Ransom Street (formerly
Shaler Street) and about 720 feet north of Braddock Ave., and the other,
demolished in 1928, was north of Braddock Ave. and 1200 feet east of
Ransom Street. This is a set of two views taken from slightly different
angles.
August 1924.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
